ACPI Component Architecture (ACPICA)

ACPI Component Architecture (ACPICA) is a reference implementation of the Advanced
Configuration and Power Interface (ACPI) specification. This implementation simplifies
complex ACPI operating system implementations by integrating it directly as a
kernel-resident subsystem, without changes to the core ACPICA code.

See: https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/topic-technology/open/acpica/overview.html

git submodule add git@github.com:amrzar/acpica.git
git submodule update --init